      <h5 class= "text-primary text-center">
        Chicago style
      </h5>
      <p>
        10 entering for the weekend (not for both days)</br>
        10 for losing your round</br>
        15 for being closest to the index in your race</br> 
        20 for being the closet to index per round (awarded to the 1 car closest to index)</br>
        10 for losing final 20 points for winning final
      </p>
      <h5>
        Examples of Total Points Earned
      </h5>
      <div>
        <ol>
          <li>
            Loser both rounds</br>
            10 +10+10=30
          </li>
          <li>
            Loser one round winner one round</br>
            10+10+15=35
          </li>
          <li>
            Winner both rounds but not in final (ie: not one of two closest to dial runs in either round)</br>
            10+15+15= 40 points
          </li>
          <li>
            Loser one round won one round w/closest to index and lose final</br>
            10+10+20+10 =50
          </li>
          <li>
            Winner one round, closest to index for round two and in final but lose race</br>
            10+15+20+10= 55
          </li>
          <li>
            Loser one round winner one round w/closest to index and win final</br>
            10+10+20+20= 60
          </li>
          <li>
            Full pull but lose final</br>
            10+20+20+10=60
          </li>
          <li>
            Full pull (win + win closest to index and win final)</br>
            10+20+20+20=70
          </li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          Maximum total two race weekend </br>
          Day one 10+20+20+20=70 (day two) +20+20+20= 130</br>
          Minimum total two race weekend </br>
          10+10+10 =30 (day two) +10+10=50 points (providing they make four runs)</br>
          Remember only 10 entering points total for weekend for Chicago style</br>
        </p>
